sql:
SELECT name
FROM audio_samples
WHERE wer > 10;

SELECT name, audio_duration, source
FROM audio_samples
ORDER BY audio_duration DESC;

SELECT source, COUNT(*) AS sample_count
FROM audio_samples
GROUP BY source;

external_knowledge:
- The top 10 most active users refers to those users who have provided the highest number of feedback entries; 
- The average word error rate (WER) and character error rate (CER) are metrics used to evaluate the quality of transcription models, with lower values indicating better performance; 
- The Cartesian product between the monthly quality statistics and the most active users allows for a comprehensive comparison of model performance across different users.
